						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in a ruined temple site to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1477, Bahudhānya Vaiśākha, 11, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Registers the consecration of the temple of Viśvanātha and also gifted land by Chiṭāmarāju, son of Yidara Mallaparāju for the merit of Veligōṭi Timmā-Nāyanigāru.</p>						

